source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-cheesy-beef-and-pepper-fajitas-6746074c127558ca79fec4eb
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Dice @tomato{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}; mince a few slices until you
have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered).
Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced).

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, a squeeze of lime juice, @salt{to taste},
and @pepper{to taste}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon} with a squeeze of lime
juice. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches
a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add green pepper; cook until lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add sliced onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and tender,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next
step) and a splash of water. Cook, stirring, until veggies are coated and water has
mostly evaporated. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Open package of @ground beef{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

> Rinse beef under cold water; pat dry with paper towels. Swap in shrimp or beef for
> pork; cook through this step as instructed (no need to break up shrimp into pieces!)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle} in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat.
Add beef and remaining Southwest spice blend; cook, stirring occasionally, until beef
is browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1%unit}, lime zest, and a squeeze of lime juice until beef is
coated and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.
Turn off heat.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with beef and veggies. Top with pico de gallo,
@Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, and lime crema. Serve with any remaining lime wedges
on the side.

> TIP: Serve beef, veggies, pico de gallo, Monterey Jack, lime crema, and lime wedges
> in separate bowls or plates for a build-your-own fajita bar!